    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offered is a pristine 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD, a masterclass in lightweight engineering. The heart is a matching-numbers 13B-REW rotary engine, featuring the factory sequential twin-turbocharger setup that provides linear power delivery across the rev range. The chassis remains exceptionally rigid, supported by its original four-wheel double-wishbone suspension and aluminum components. Shifts are crisp through the five-speed manual gearbox, paired with a factory Torsen limited-slip differential. Every vacuum line has been inspected, and the cooling system remains at peak efficiency. This example retains its factory-spec aerodynamics and lightweight alloy wheels, presenting in a condition rarely seen outside of a private collection.",
